This paper deals with computational geometry, specifically the problem of computing the geodesic center of a simple polygon. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category. The algorithm presented in the paper involves constructing a shortest path tree, which is a data structure commonly used in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the time and space complexity of the algorithm, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of finding the geodesic center can also be viewed as a graph problem, which falls under the category of Graph Theory (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves a time-space trade-off, which is a common topic in the field of Compiler Construction (cs.CC).
